# /component — Create Component

## Usage
```
/component [name] [type]
```

**Types**: `ui` | `feature` | `page`

## Component Types

| Type | Purpose | Directory |
|------|---------|-----------|
| `ui` | Atomic, reusable, no business logic | `src/components/ui/` |
| `feature` | Domain-specific, receives data via props | `src/components/{domain}/` |
| `page` | Route component, uses compositor hook | `src/pages/{domain}/` |

## Phases

### Phase 0 — Reconnaissance
1. Read existing components to understand patterns
2. Check design system and color tokens
3. Read rules in `.claude/rules/`

### Phase 1 — Create Component

**UI Component** (atomic):
- `forwardRef` for composition
- `cn()` for class merging
- Props interface with `className?`
- `displayName` set
- Skeleton companion for loading

**Feature Component** (domain):
- Typed props with dedicated interface
- Receives data via props (no fetch)
- Handles states: loading, error, empty, success
- Responsive (mobile-first)

**Page Component** (route):
- Thin shell (~40-60 lines)
- Uses compositor hook for data
- Feature component composition
- Layout and routing

### Phase 2 — Tests
- Renders without crash
- Displays correct content based on props
- Click/interaction handlers
- States: loading, error, empty

### Phase 3 — Validation
- Run tests
- Check lint

## Checklist
- [ ] All visual states (loading/error/empty/success)
- [ ] Responsive (mobile-first)
- [ ] No hardcoded colors (uses tokens)
- [ ] Dark mode functional
- [ ] Typed props interface
- [ ] Basic accessibility (labels, contrast, keyboard)
- [ ] Tests covering main scenarios
- [ ] No business logic in component
